s=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\"><svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>Most people in the Church today still haven’t touched ChatGPT. They’ve heard the term “AI” floating around, but it feels distant—a tech fad, a Silicon Valley toy, a problem for someone else’s kids.</p><p>But something far bigger is emerging.</p><p>We are standing at the threshold of <strong>AGI—Artificial General Intelligence</strong>—a form of intelligence that doesn’t just answer questions, but can learn anything, adapt to anything, and <a href=\"https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGGV886mE6FE6Ju5u4YzYMpPhRSnMXzz6&amp;si=zfWpWKrnjZseApu6\">outperform humans across </a><em><a href=\"https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGGV886mE6FE6Ju5u4YzYMpPhRSnMXzz6&amp;si=zfWpWKrnjZseApu6\">every</a></em><a href=\"https://youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGGV886mE6FE6Ju5u4YzYMpPhRSnMXzz6&amp;si=zfWpWKrnjZseApu6\"> cognitive task</a>.</p><p>This is not science fiction. This is not fearmongering. This is simply the world your children will inherit.</p><p>And the question before us is not whether this technology will arrive, but <strong>what kind of humans we will become</strong> as it does.</p><p>The Christian answer is neither fear nor escape.<br><strong>It is incarnation.</strong></p>"}